---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — TED Talk Finder | AI-Powered TED Talk Discovery"
  description="Read our Privacy Policy to understand how TED Talk Finder handles data, including details on our integration with YouTube API Services and AI curation engines."
  canonicalUrl="https://tedtalksfinder.com/privacy-policy"
>
  <!-- Nav -->
  <Header />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-black text-white py-16 sm:py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p
        class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#EB0028] mb-4"
      >
        Legal Information
      </p>
      <h1
        class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight leading-none mb-6"
      >
        Privacy<br /><span class="text-[#EB0028]">Policy</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-400 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Your privacy is important to us. This policy outlines how TED Talk
        Finder operates, what data we process, and how we work with third-party
        service providers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="bg-white py-12 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-12">
      <section
        class="prose max-w-none text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6"
      >
        <div>
          <h2
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mb-3 border-b border-gray-200 pb-2"
          >
            1. Overview
          </h2>
          <p>
            TED Talk Finder is a free, web-based search and curation utility
            designed to help users discover TED talks on various topics. We do
            not require user registration, accounts, or personal log-in
            information. You are free to use our utility anonymously.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mb-3 border-b border-gray-200 pb-2"
          >
            2. Information We Collect
          </h2>
          <p>We do not collect or store any personal data. Specifically:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong>No Accounts:</strong> You do not need to register, log in, or
              provide an email address to use our search utility.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Search Queries:</strong> Queries submitted through the search
              form are processed to generate AI recommendations and verify them. We
              do not store queries alongside identifying information.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>IP Addresses:</strong> We apply a daily rate-limiting policy
              (maximum 20 searches per day per IP address) to prevent API abuse. This
              limit is processed in-memory and is not linked to any personal profiles.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mb-3 border-b border-gray-200 pb-2"
          >
            3. Third-Party Service Providers
          </h2>
          <p>
            To deliver AI recommendations and search results, our utility
            integrates with several third-party service providers:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-3">
            <li>
              <strong>Google Gemini API &amp; xAI Grok API:</strong> We utilize artificial
              intelligence models provided by Google and xAI to suggest relevant TED
              talks. No personal data is sent to these models; only the user-submitted
              search term is provided.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>YouTube API Services:</strong> We use YouTube API Services to
              verify the existence, titles, durations, publication dates, and thumbnails
              of suggested talks. By using this application, you agree to be bound
              by the YouTube Terms of Service (<a
                href="https://www.youtube.com/t/terms"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-[#EB0028] hover:underline"
                >https://www.youtube.com/t/terms</a
              >) and Google Privacy Policy (<a
                href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-[#EB0028] hover:underline"
                >https://policies.google.com/privacy</a
              >).
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mb-3 border-b border-gray-200 pb-2"
          >
            4. Cookies and Local Caching
          </h2>
          <p>
            We do not use tracking cookies or persistent advertising
            identifiers. We may use local browser storage (such as
            SessionStorage) or server in-memory caching to save popular search
            results to minimize external API usage and improve performance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mb-3 border-b border-gray-200 pb-2"
          >
            5. Updates to This Policy
          </h2>
          <p>
            We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We encourage
            visitors to frequently check this page for any changes. Your
            continued use of this site after any change in this Privacy Policy
            will constitute your acceptance of such change.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2
            class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-black mb-3 border-b border-gray-200 pb-2"
          >
            6. Contact Us
          </h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions or feedback regarding this Privacy Policy,
            please contact us by visiting our <a
              href="/contact"
              class="text-[#EB0028] hover:underline">Contact Page</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <section class="bg-black text-white p-8 sm:p-12 text-center mt-12">
        <p
          class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#EB0028] mb-4"
        >
          Start Discovering
        </p>
        <h2
          class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight mb-4"
        >
          Ready to Discover More?
        </h2>
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-block bg-[#EB0028] text-white font-extrabold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs sm:text-sm px-8 py-4 hover:bg-[#c40020] transition-colors duration-150"
        >
          Find Talks Now
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer
    class="bg-black text-white py-10 px-4 sm:py-12 sm:px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-gray-900"
  >
    <div
      class="max-w-7xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center text-[10px] sm:text-xs text-gray-600 gap-4 text-center sm:text-left"
    >
      <div>
        &copy; 2026 TED Talk Finder. Built with Astro &amp; Tailwind CSS v4.
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 sm:gap-4">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
        <a href="/about" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">About</a>
        <a
          href="/privacy-policy"
          class="hover:text-white transition-colors text-white"
          >Privacy Policy</a
        >
        <a
          href="/terms-and-conditions"
          class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Terms</a
        >
        <a href="/contact" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Contact</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
